rComments: Gave standard grades and replied quickly to questions or concerns

Excellent communicator! Very clear. Assignments/exams were really easy if you read the material. Only con: You NEED to absolutely do all/most of the readings to do well on his test questions. Not really a problem because the readings are all interesting material.
Best professor at U of T!! Cares very much for his students, and ensures test material, assignment deadlines, and grading are fair.

Awesome teacher, really cares about his students since he likes to make sure everything is fair. He's passionate about his work and includes information in the biotechnology that we students want to know about.

Although one of the busiest professors on campus, he takes the time to individually cater to students. One of the most engaging professors I have ever met, and one whose main goal is to get you to love his work-and believe me if you dont at the beginning of the year, you will by the time his course is over. FIND THOMPSON and take all of his classes
Paul Thompson is a kind of person you would dream to have as your grandfather - extremely caring, attentive to every question, kind and warm.

Deals with the themes of the course too superficially. Major flaw is therefore lack of in-depth & substantial analysis/discussion of any of the issues. And his views on postmodernism is just plain wrong/biased/ill-informed. Overall pedagogical skills not bad though.
